('Harris, W. E.; Racine, R.', 'The globular cluster NGC 6934', 'Astronomical Journal 78, 242', 'http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1973AJ.....78..242H', 307, '2012-12-04 10:02:43', 1973, '', '2012-12-04', NULL, NULL, '', 'New photoelectric and photographic photometry in B and V is presented for the globular cluster NGC 6934. The color-magnitude diagram is determined down to V around 18 and is basically similar to that for M3. An evenly populated horizontal branch appears at V(HB) = 16.82 +/- 0.02. The reddening, estimated from the position of the RR Lyrae strip, is E(B-V) = 0.20 +/- 0.02, giving a distance modulus (m-M)o=15.6. Brief discussion of the variable stars and of the cluster luminosity function are included.', 160),
